  "prompt": "Can someone screenshot a snap after I block them?",
  "response": "When you block someone on Snapchat, they can no longer view your content, send you messages, or interact with you in any way. If they had previously opened a snap from you before you blocked them, they might have taken a screenshot of it then, but they cannot take a screenshot of your content after you block them. \n\nHowever, it's important to note that if they were quick enough to take a screenshot before you blocked them, they would still have that screenshot. Also, blocking someone does not erase the previous messages or snaps they may have saved.",
